cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.RO

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision (CV) and proposes a new deep learning architecture for detecting vanishing points in images. Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also introduces a new convolutional operator, which involves learning geometric properties of vanishing points, and this is related to machine learning (LG) and artificial intelligence (AI). Additionally, the paper deals with geometric properties of lines and intersections, which is related to graphics (GR) and robotics (RO).
